HEADWORD: Bonify
<hw>Bon"i*fy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bonus</ets> good + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>bonifier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To convert into, or make,
good.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>bonify</qex> evils, or tincture them with good.</q>
<rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boniness</ent>⟦br⟧
